Rebrand user-data paths and PWA install name to Composery

Renames code-server's config/data/extensions directory from `code-server` to
`composery` (so user settings live at ~/.local/share/composery/User/settings.json
and config at ~/.config/composery) and defaults the PWA install name to
"Composery". These are the surfaces a browser user actually reaches. The
code-server CLI binary, IPC socket/mutex names, /tmp scratch dir, and upstream
URLs are intentionally left untouched (build/runtime machinery, never user-visible).

